The word '''jolly''' can be used as either a noun or an adjective.

*A jolly is an event which is perceived to be more enjoyable than useful, and is perhaps a freebie too
*A jolly can mean "very", as in a "jolly good show"
*A jolly is a party or celebration.

People use it in phrases such as "get your jollies," "have a jolly good time," and in the song"
"For he's a jolly good fellow..."

==As a name==

*Jolly is a name that is found in some name books.  It is listed as an "unusual" name and shares the same meaning as the [[French language|French]] name, Jolie.  It is derived from the Old French word, "joli" that means "merriness."

*The name is quite popular in Southern [[India]] where the French once visited and settled.  It is also used as a result of the [[United Kingdom|British]] presence.

*Jolly is a unisex first name in South India.

*Jolly is the surname of a family of southern [[Germany|German]] scientists and politicians including [[Julius Jolly]].

